      <h1 class="mb-4">üßô‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è Restmancer API ‚Äì User Endpoints</h1>

      <p>This page documents the available REST endpoints for fetching user data from the Restmancer API.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2>GET <code>/api/users</code></h2>
      <p>Returns a list of all users.</p>
      <h5>Optional Query Parameters:</h5>
      <ul>
        <li><code>limit</code> ‚Äì Number of users to return.</li>
      </ul>
      <h6>Examples:</h6>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/api/users" target="_blank">/api/users</a></li>
        <li><a href="/api/users?limit=3" target="_blank">/api/users?limit=3</a></li>
      </ul>

      <hr />

      <h2>GET <code>/api/users/custom</code></h2>
      <p>Returns only specific fields of users, optionally with a limit.</p>
      <h5>Required Query Parameters:</h5>
      <ul>
        <li><code>field</code> ‚Äì Comma-separated list of fields (e.g., <code>name,email</code>).</li>
      </ul>
      <h5>Optional:</h5>
      <ul>
        <li><code>limit</code> ‚Äì Limit number of users to return.</li>
      </ul>
      <h6>Examples:</h6>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/api/users/custom?field=name,email" target="_blank">/api/users/custom?field=name,email</a></li>
        <li><a href="/api/users/custom?field=name,email&limit=2" target="_blank">/api/users/custom?field=name,email&limit=2</a></li>
      </ul>

      <hr />

